    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In 1760, William Allen and Joseph Turner founded the Andover Iron Works, sparking the borough’s early industrial boom.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/andover_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "During the Revolution, the iron works was seized by the Continental Congress on January 15, 1778, after Allen and Turner fled as Loyalists.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/andover_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Precambrian schists and gneisses beneath Andover have long supplied the iron ore that powered its historic mines.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/andover_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Andover experiences a humid continental climate, with snowy winters and warm, humid summers that reflect its northern New Jersey location.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        9
